parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of airbag sensors and failure to deploy airbags in the event of an accident can lead to serious injury or even fatalities.
symptoms: Dashboard warning lights (I code 95
ABS
traction
and airbag/seatbelt lights)
airbag failure to deploy in accidents
malfunctioning passenger side sensor
malfunctioning right front bumper sensor
and incorrect diagnostic results.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake failure and malfunction can cause accidents, especially on highways, and lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Smoke coming from the brakes
brake booster and other parts failure
and brake malfunction while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Improper airbag deployment can cause serious injuries, including lacerations and broken bones.
symptoms: Airbag deployment with metal or plastic fragments
causing injury
and inadequate damage to the vehicle considering the severity of the injury.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The accelerator pedal sticking to the floorboard can cause the vehicle to accelerate uncontrollably, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal feels stuck to the floorboard
the vehicle accelerates uncontrollably
no warning lights are illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the airbag system can lead to the failure of the airbags to deploy in the event of a crash, potentially causing serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light comes on
the airbag code is displayed on the dashboard
the airbag system fails to function properly
the airbag system malfunctions intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The false triggering of the alarm can cause unnecessary noise, disturbance, and inconvenience to the vehicle owner and surrounding individuals, potentially leading to battery drain and other electrical system issues.
symptoms: The alarm sounds when the vehicle is parked and unattended
with no apparent reason or trigger
no one is around the vehicle
the alarm is loud and persistent
the alarm may drain the battery if it continues to sound for an extended period.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loud noise and ineffective braking can cause a loss of control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Loud noise when braking
feeling of the car not stopping or slowing down
repeated occurrences of the problem despite multiple visits to the dealer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The dealer's inability to diagnose and fix the problem can lead to a loss of trust and confidence in the dealership, and potentially compromise the safety of the vehicle.
symptoms: Dealer unable to diagnose the problem
repeated visits to the dealer without a resolution
lack of concern for customer safety.
